  volume    =  126,
  number    = "Pt 6",
  pages     = "1488--1497",
  abstract  = "DNA repair has long been considered impossible in human
               spermatozoa due to the high level of DNA compaction observed in
               these cells. However, detailed examination of the base excision
               repair pathway in human spermatozoa has revealed the presence of
