  volume    =  161,
  pages     = "98--105",
  abstract  = "Clonal hematopoiesis of indeterminate potential (CHIP) is the
               presence of a clonally expanded hematopoietic stem cell caused by
               a leukemogenic mutation in individuals without evidence of
               hematologic malignancy, dysplasia, or cytopenia. CHIP is
               associated with a 0.5-1.0\% risk per year of leukemia.
