               these are as numerous as associations with established genetic
               markers such as driver gene alterations. Signatures of prior
               exposures to DNA damaging agents - including chemotherapy - tend
               to associate with drug resistance, while signatures of
               deficiencies in DNA repair tend to predict sensitivity towards
               particular therapeutics. Replication analyses across independent
               drug and CRISPR genetic screening data sets reveal hundreds of
               robust associations, which are provided as a resource for drug
               repurposing guided by mutational signature markers.",
