  journal   = "Nat. Commun.",
  publisher = "Nature Publishing Group",
  volume    =  16,
  number    =  1,
  pages     =  4527,
  abstract  = "De novo germline mutation is an important factor in the evolution
               of allelic diversity and disease predisposition in a population.
               Here, we study the influence of genetically-inferred ancestry and
               environmental factors on de novo mutation rates and spectra.
               Using a genetically diverse sample of ~10 K whole-genome
