  volume    =  483,
  number    =  7391,
  pages     = "603--607",
  abstract  = "The systematic translation of cancer genomic data into knowledge
               of tumour biology and therapeutic possibilities remains
               challenging. Such efforts should be greatly aided by robust
               preclinical model systems that reflect the genomic diversity of
               human cancers and for which detailed genetic and pharmacological
               annotation is available. Here we describe the Cancer Cell Line
               Encyclopedia (CCLE): a compilation of gene expression,
               chromosomal copy number and massively parallel sequencing data
               from 947 human cancer cell lines. When coupled with
               pharmacological profiles for 24 anticancer drugs across 479 of
               the cell lines, this collection allowed identification of
               genetic, lineage, and gene-expression-based predictors of drug
