               during late spermatogenesis can induce damage that persists in
               the fertilizing sperm and that the risk of embryos with
               paternally transmitted chromosomal aberrations depends on the
               efficiency of maternal DNA repair during the first cycle after
               fertilization. We show that female mice with defective DNA
