  publisher = "Elsevier BV",
  volume    =  56,
  number    =  1,
  pages     = "110--156",
  abstract  = "The number of nongonadal nuclei in the free-living soil nematode
               Caenorhabditis elegans increases from about 550 in the newly
               hatched larva to about 810 in the mature hermaphrodite and to
               about 970 in the mature male. The pattern of cell divisions which
