  pages     = "a012708",
  abstract  = "The structural features that enable replicative DNA polymerases
               to synthesize DNA rapidly and accurately also limit their ability
               to copy damaged DNA. Direct replication of DNA damage is termed
               translesion synthesis (TLS), a mechanism conserved from bacteria
