  volume    =  312,
  number    =  2,
  pages     = "335--346",
  abstract  = "We describe here the error specificity of mammalian DNA
               polymerase eta (pol eta), an enzyme that performs translesion DNA
               synthesis and may participate in somatic hypermutation of
               immunoglobulin genes. Both mouse and human pol eta lack intrinsic
               proofreading exonuclease activity and both copy undamaged DNA
