  number    =  4,
  pages     = "662--673",
  abstract  = "DNA polymerase theta (Pol θ)-mediated end joining (TMEJ) has been
               implicated in the repair of chromosome breaks, but its cellular
               mechanism and role relative to canonical repair pathways are
               poorly understood. We show that it accounts for most repairs
