               cells against a wide range of DNA damaging agents, including UV,
               γ-irradiation, cisplatin, and methyl methane sulphonate (MMS).
               POLK-1 acts specifically but redundantly with POLH-1 in
               protection against methylation damage. Importantly, both
               polymerases play a prominent role early in embryonic development
