  volume    =  31,
  number    =  9,
  pages     = "1582--1589",
  abstract  = "Mutation is the source of genetic variation and the fundament of
               evolution. Temperature has long been suggested to have a direct
               impact on realized spontaneous mutation rates. If mutation rates
               vary in response to environmental conditions, such as the
               variation of the ambient temperature through space and time, they
               should no longer be described as species-specific constants. By
