  pages     = "573--580",
  abstract  = "A tandem repeat in DNA is two or more contiguous, approximate
               copies of a pattern of nucleotides. Tandem repeats have been
               shown to cause human disease, may play a variety of regulatory
               and evolutionary roles and are important laboratory and analytic
               tools. Extensive knowledge about pattern size, copy number,
