               However, we find that the maternal age effect is not confined to
               known hotspots of oocyte mutagenesis, nor are postzygotic
               mutations likely to contribute significantly. STR nucleotide
               composition demonstrates divergent effects on de novo mutation
               (DNM) rates between sexes. Unlike the paternal lineage,
               maternally derived DNMs at A/T STRs display a significantly
               greater association with maternal age than DNMs at G/C-containing
               STRs. These observations may suggest the mechanism and
