  volume    =  31,
  number    =  8,
  pages     = "1313--1324",
  abstract  = "There are more than 55,000 variable number tandem repeats (VNTRs)
               in the human genome, notable for both their striking polymorphism
               and mutability. Despite their role in human evolution and genomic
               variation, they have yet to be studied collectively and in
               detail, partially owing to their large size, variability, and
