               computational and biochemical results demonstrate that iMSs are
               abundant in human genomes and are sources of population-specific
               genetic variation that may affect genome stability. The
               genome-wide identification of iMSs in human populations presented
               here has important implications for current models describing the
               impact of microsatellite polymorphisms on gene expression.",
  month     =  jul,
  year      =  2014,
  language  = "en"
