               heritability of height from empirical genome-wide
               identity-by-descent sharing, which varied from 0.374 to 0.617
               (mean 0.498, standard deviation 0.036). The variance in
               identity-by-descent sharing per chromosome and per genome was
               consistent with theory. The maximum likelihood estimate of the
               heritability for height was 0.80 with no evidence for non-genetic
               causes of sib resemblance, consistent with results from
               independent twin and family studies but using an entirely
               separate source of information. Our application shows that it is
