  publisher = "Oxford University Press (OUP)",
  volume    =  7,
  number    =  7,
  abstract  = "Abstract SV-plaudit is a framework for rapidly curating
               structural variant (SV) predictions. For each SV, we generate an
               image that visualizes the coverage and alignment signals from a
               set of samples. Images are uploaded to our cloud framework where
               users assess the quality of each image using a client-side web
               application. Reports can then be generated as a tab-delimited
               file or annotated Variant Call Format (VCF) file. As a proof of
               principle, nine researchers collaborated for 1 hour to evaluate
               1,350 SVs each. We anticipate that SV-plaudit will become a
               standard step in variant calling pipelines and the crowd-sourced
               curation of other biological results. Code available at
