  abstract = "The advent of modern DNA sequencing technology is the driving
              force in obtaining complete intra-specific genomes that can be
              used to detect loci that have been subject to positive selection
              in the recent past. Based on selective sweep theory, beneficial
              loci can be detected by examining the single nucleotide
              polymorphism patterns in intraspecific genome alignments. In the
