  journal  = "Nat. Commun.",
  volume   =  7,
  pages    =  12989,
  abstract = "Structural variation (SV) represents a major source of differences
              between individual human genomes and has been linked to disease
              phenotypes. However, the majority of studies provide neither a
              global view of the full spectrum of these variants nor integrate
              them into reference panels of genetic variation. Here, we analyse
              whole genome sequencing data of 769 individuals from 250 Dutch
              families, and provide a haplotype-resolved map of 1.9 million
