              gamete; crossovers partially protected chromosomes from
              nondisjunction at the meiosis I cell division. Some chromosomes
              and donors underwent more-frequent nondisjunction during meiosis
              I, and others showed more meiosis II segregation failures. Sperm
              genomes also manifested many genomic anomalies that could not be
