  number    =  18,
  pages     = "2984--2990.e3",
  abstract  = "SummaryCrossovers (COs) are formed during meiosis by the repair
               of programmed DNA double-strand breaks (DSBs) and are required
               for the proper segregation of chromosomes. More DSBs are made
               than COs, and the remaining DSBs are repaired as noncrossovers
