  pages    = "710--722",
  abstract = "Neandertals, the closest evolutionary relatives of present-day
              humans, lived in large parts of Europe and western Asia before
              disappearing 30,000 years ago. We present a draft sequence of the
              Neandertal genome composed of more than 4 billion nucleotides from
              three individuals. Comparisons of the Neandertal genome to the
